  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\n@truffle/resolver's `resolve` method only takes absolute paths as argument, which may have made sense previously, but now we use `project:/` style paths internally in Truffle these days. For consistency, this method should be expanded to support this new prefixing.\r\n\r\n(This issue most directly spun out of #2114)\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n- Require @truffle/resolver\r\n- Call `resolve()` with a `project:/`-style path to a source\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nIt should resolve to the source\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nIt does not resolve to a source\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: \r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.7.9\r\n* node version (`node --version`):\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): \r\n",
